    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - CAB ACCESSORIES -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Testing Dual Axis Motorized Mirrors
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Testing Dual Axis Motorized Mirrors</title>
        <table id="t0819312" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Dual Axis Motorized Mirrors</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="1.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.08in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check 15A fuse F5-A for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F5-A</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (1137) from motorized mirror switch. Turn key on. At connector
                                (1137) measure voltage to ground at circuit 78C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(1137), 78C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 78C from fuse, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At connector (1137) measure voltage between circuits 78C and 78-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(1137), 78C to 78-GA.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78-GA path to gnd, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to left position. Push the knob to up position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to D) and (H to C).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to D) and (H to C).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to left position. Push the knob to down position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to C) and (H to D).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to C) and (H and D).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to left position. Push the knob to right position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to B) and (H to C).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch (A to B) and H to C).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to left position. Push the knob to left position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to C) and (H to B).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to C) and (H to B).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to right position. Push the knob to up position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to E) and (H to F).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to E) and (H to F).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to right position. Push the knob to down position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to F) and (H to E).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to F) and (H to E).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to right position. Push the knob to left position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to F) and (H to G).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to F) and (H to G).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Turn the mirror switch (1137) knob to right position. Push the knob to right position,
                                measure resistance from terminals (A to G) and (H to F).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Mirror switch, (A to G) and (H to F).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With switch (1137) in neutral position, measure resistance between all of the
                                terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>All mirror switch terminals.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect connector (1137). Turn ignition key to ACC position. Verify operation of the
                                left mirror.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Check left mirror operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Left mirror operates correctly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 15.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Verify operation of the right mirror.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" align="center">
                            <para>Right mirror operates correctly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Mirror circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to step 17.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (70) going to the left mirror. Turn the switch knob to the "L"
                                position. Have an assistant hold the switch in the up position. Measure voltage from
                                middle pin of the three small connectors, to the next pin counter- clockwise from the
                                middle pin.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(70), 58B to 78F.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#177; 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 58B, 78F, 78P or 78R, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Have an assistant hold the switch in the left position. Measure voltage between two
                                outer pins of the three small connectors of connector (70).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(70), 78F to 78E.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#177; 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Left mirror circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78E, 78N, 78P or 78F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (70) going to the right mirror. Turn the switch knob to the "R"
                                position. Have an assistant hold the switch in the up position. Measure voltage from
                                middle pin of the three small connectors, to the next pin counter- clockwise from the
                                middle pin.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(70), 58B to 78F.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#177; 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 58B, 78F or 78S, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Have an assistant hold the switch in the left position. Measure voltage between two
                                outer pins of the three small connectors of connector (70).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(70), 78F to 78E.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#177; 12 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Right mirror circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 78E or 78F, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
